25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12719.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Goodbye 2D</span><hr size=1> Well, there are still 2D TV shows, but even those seem to be in danger. A LOT of new 2D shows that are made now (especially many of them on Adult Swim) aren't traditional 2D, they're done with Flash or some other program. That, or they're just cheaply produced. It works for some shows, but it seems like a bad trend.<br>
<br>
And I don't think that Disney getting out of 2D opens the door for others. Not really anyway. Like I said, almost everyone who's attempted 2D films in the past that wasn't Disney has failed to be successful, while on the other hand, several other companies besides Disney have created hugely successful 3D animated films. That tells me that people in general don't care about 2D films, and Disney was about the only company around that could have done something about that. <br>
<br>
Who knows, maybe in several years when all we see are 3D movies, then people will get nostalgic about 2D and we'll see a few. But for right now, I think we're screwed.<br>
<br>
And like I mentioned in my first post, this isn't the only place it's happening. Big name 2D games are so few and far between it's pathetic. Sure, everyone points you to the GBA, but I want NEW games with NEW technology. All the old games have to be done in 3D now just for anyone to enjoy them, which is fine sometimes. I mean, I enjoy 3D games as much as anyone, and it's interesting to see old games redone in full 3D. What really bothers me is that 2D is so worthless now, that even games that ARE 2D aren't hand drawn, they're rendered in 3D. The newest Megaman games are good examples of this. I'm not asking for much, I realize that 3D games are more popular and there are many things you can do that you can't in 2D, but that goes both ways. Would it be that difficult to make a high profile 2D game for the next gen systems every now and then? <p><html>
