<br>
And MonkeyPunch, that's exactly what I'm thinking. There is so much potential for 2D games on current hardware, but no one takes advantage of it. They could make some absolutely gorgeous games. Not only are the machines more powerful, but they have more space on the disc formats to store everything.<br>
<br>
And anime is fine, I like it of course, but it's not everything. And even they are starting to overuse 3D, though they usually try to integrate it into 2D animation. Most of the time, it looks horrible.<br>
<br>
And the other problem is that there's less exchange if there's no real US 2D animation anymore. Prism brought up comics, and that's a good parallel. There's a lot of influencing on both sides going on. They're both different, and they both have their good and bad qualities. As long as they both exist, they can learn from one another, and influence each other. It's not going to happen if there's nothing there.<br>
